<HL>
   Business Brief -- International Banknote Co.:
   Merger With U.S. Banknote
   Approved by Shareholders
</HL>
<DATE>
07/27/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C13
</SO>
<CO>
   UBK WNEWS
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
</IN>
<LP>
   International Banknote Co. shareholders approved a merger
with U.S. Banknote Co. L.P.
   Under the terms of the agreement between the two New York
companies, each International Banknote common share has been
converted into one-fourth preferred share with a liquidation
value of $18 a share and one-half common share of the
combined company.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Shares of the new company, U.S. Banknote Corp., will trade
on a "when issued" basis on the American Stock Exchange under
the symbol UBK; yesterday the shares were quoted at an
indicated range of $2.50 to $3 a share. The company will have
eight million common and 1.5 million preferred shares
outstanding.
   U.S. Banknote Co., a printer of securities and currency
and producer of three-dimensional holograms used on credit
cards, will have estimated combined sales of about $135
million this year, said Morris Weissman, former chairman and
chief executive officer, who retains those titles at the new
company. Stanley Kreitman, former president, was named
president and chief operating officer of the new company.
</TEXT>
